Description: β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
transcription terminator for bacteriophage T7 RNA polymerase
bidirectional E. coli tonB-P14 transcription terminator
strong E. coli promoter; hybrid between the trp and lac UV5 promoters

The lac repressor binds to the lac operator to inhibit transcription in E. coli. This inhibition can be relieved by adding lactose or isopropyl-β-D-thiogalactopyranoside (IPTG). The symmetric lac operator was optimized for tight binding of lac repressor. lac repressor encoded by lacI
LacZα fragment of β-galactosidase; lacZ fragment
